	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: PPU render timing basic questions</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Petruza wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">And what about $4014 AKA Sprite DMA?<br />I know it's too slow to do mid-scanline effects, but can this be used during render, for example, to show more than 64 sprites?</div>
<br />
<br />$4014 is just a CPU macro that fetches bytes and feeds them to $2004 one after another, so all rules that apply to $2004 apply to $4014

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


